        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 10:55AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1055 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Baker, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Baker and Willard.
</description>
        <instruction>Be prepared for small hail, gusty winds, and cloud to ground
lightning.</instruction>
